"1130–Male":"1130–Deceased","1131–Female":"1131–Deceased","1238":"1238","1145":"1145","1175":"1175","1131":"1131","1153":"1153","1130":"1130","1 January 1175":"1 January 1175","about 1153":"about 1153","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales","Andea, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Cardigan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish (Tipperary, Leitrim and Cavan): variant of   Corrigan  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Corrigan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Malachy, Brendan, Dermot, Bridgid, Brigid, Cait, Niall, Patrick Michael.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Corragáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Corragán</i>’, a double diminutive of <i>corr</i> ‘pointed’."]}]},{"name":"Isolda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The name of the tragic mistress of Tristan in the Arthurian romances. There are several versions of the story. The main features are that the beautiful Isolde, an Irish princess, is betrothed to the aged King Mark of Cornwall. However, through accidentally drinking a magic potion, she and the young Cornish knight Tristan fall in love, with tragic consequences. The story has exercised a powerful hold on the European imagination. The name was relatively common in Britain in the Middle Ages, but is much rarer today."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Isolda de Cardigan was born about 1153, in Cardiganshire, Wales, her father, Andrew de Cardigan, was 25 and her mother, Ela of Cardigan, was 23. She married Gilbert de Andea in Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in 1175, in Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 23."},"et":{"about 1153–1175":"umbes 1153–1175","1153–1175":"1153–1175","1145–1175":"1145–1175","1175–1238":"1175–1238","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1131–Female":"1131–Surnud","1238":"1238","1145":"1145","1175":"1175","1131":"1131","1153":"1153","1130":"1130","1 January 1175":"1. jaanuar 1175","about 1153":"umbes 1153","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales","Andea, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1153–1175":"noin 1153–1175","1153–1175":"1153–1175","1145–1175":"1145–1175","1175–1238":"1175–1238","1130–Male":"1130–Kuollut","1131–Female":"1131–Kuollut","1238":"1238","1145":"1145","1175":"1175","1131":"1131","1153":"1153","1130":"1130","1 January 1175":"1. tammikuuta 1175","about 1153":"noin 1153","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales","Andea, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1153–1175":"environ 1153–1175","1153–1175":"1153–1175","1145–1175":"1145–1175","1175–1238":"1175–1238","1130–Male":"1130–Décédé","1131–Female":"1131–Décédée","1238":"1238","1145":"1145","1175":"1175","1131":"1131","1153":"1153","1130":"1130","1 January 1175":"1 janvier 1175","about 1153":"environ 1153","Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Galles","Andea, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardiganshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Wales":"Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":